# Root .dockerignore — applied to every Docker build whose context is the
# monorepo root (i.e. apps/web and apps/api-gateway, which need access to
# the workspace package.json files at root + packages/*).
#
# Why this file matters specifically for the workspace:
#   pnpm creates symlinks at apps/<name>/node_modules/@slothbox/<pkg>
#   pointing back into ../../../packages/<pkg>. When BuildKit transfers the
#   build context to the daemon, walking through node_modules trips on
#   those symlinks and aborts with "invalid file request" before any
#   COPY runs. Excluding **/node_modules sidesteps the entire issue —
#   the Dockerfiles re-create node_modules inside the image via their own
#   `pnpm install` step anyway, so we never want the host's copy in the
#   build context.

# pnpm / yarn / npm lockstep
**/node_modules

# Build outputs from previous local runs
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/.cache
**/out
**/dist
**/coverage
**/.next/cache

# .NET intermediate / bin
**/bin
**/obj
**/*.dll.config

# Go build cache
**/vendor

# Editor + OS noise
**/.vscode
**/.idea
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.swp

# Secrets — never go into a layer. .env.example is the public template.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# Logs
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*
**/pnpm-debug.log*

# Git internals (BuildKit can resolve refs from them, but it bloats context)
.git
.gitignore
.github

# Documentation that doesn't influence the runtime image. README is small
# enough that some Dockerfiles intentionally COPY it for `--help` output;
# keep it in by default.
**/REVIEW_REPORT.md
**/STATE.md

# Test fixtures + recordings
**/test-results
**/playwright-report
**/coverage

# Local docker / compose state
docker-compose.override.yml
